                        <interp inst="t18361024-name-122" type="surname" value="LONG"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361024-name-122" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES LONG</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep a chop-house and keep-shop in Cannon-street. The prisoner was frequently a customer at my house, for some years—he came on Friday, the 30th of September—I gave my servant directions, and in consequence of what she told me after he left, I went after he left, I went after him, and found him at the bottom of London Bridge steps—I said, "I believe you have got something belonging to me"—he said he had not—I said he had—I took off his hat, and there was a tumbler in it, with my name marked on it—another was found at his lodging, with my name on it.</p>
